</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C35FAEEFF47AFF9556A2FE012630FCA8" pageId="22" pageNumber="523" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BFAFD64F47AFF9556A2FE0125D9FCE0" blockId="22.[151,1436,474,895]" pageId="22" pageNumber="523">
<emphasis id="B9312176F47AFF9556A2FE012476FDC0" bold="true" box="[199,321,510,535]" pageId="22" pageNumber="523">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="137EE1E1F47AFF955737FE0124AFFDC0" box="[338,408,510,535]" captionStart="FIGURES 5 – 8" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1982,2005]" captionTargetBox="[197,1379,232,1912]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[152,1435,193,2007]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 5 – 8. Dorsal habitus of Limnophora species: 5. Limnophora parallelifrons Emden. 6. Limnophora perfidodes Emden. 7. Limnophora simulans Stein. 8. Limnophora translucida Stein." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/242397/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="523">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
). Body length 4.0–5.0 mm; general colour brown; scutum with grey pollinose areas at the insertions of posterior presutural dorsocentral, posterior postsutural dorsocentral and apical scutellar setae; upper part of postpronotum and notopleuron grey pollinose; frons brown; face and parafacial silver pollinose; antenna, arista and palpus brown; haltere yellow; legs brown; male holoptic; frontal triangle short; arista plumose; postsutural dorsocentrals 3, all long; scutellum with long basal and apical pairs of setae and with numerous setulae on disc; lower katepisternal inserted closer to the long posterior one; lower calypter about twice the length of the upper one; wing a little infuscated, costal spine absent; fore tibia without a submedian seta; mid femur with 2 preapical setae, one posterior and one posterodorsal; mid tibia with 2 posterior setae; sternite 1 bare; sternite 5 as in 
<figureCitation id="137EE1E1F47AFF9556F2FCE125DEFCE0" box="[151,233,798,823]" captionStart="FIGURES 73 – 88" captionStartId="23.[151,264,1941,1964]" captionTargetBox="[189,1406,191,1889]" captionTargetId="figure@23.[179,1408,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="FIGURES 73 – 88. Sternite 5; cercal plate and surstyli in dorsal view; epandrium, cercal plate and surstyli in lateral view; aedeagus in lateral view: 73 – 76. Limnophora parallelifrons Emden. 77 – 80. Limnophora perfida Stein. 81 – 84. Limnophora perfidodes Emden. 85 – 88. Limnophora praeapicalis Emden." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/242402/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="523">Fig. 81</figureCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFAFD64F47AFF9556A2FCBD2191FC8C" blockId="22.[151,1436,474,895]" box="[199,1190,834,859]" pageId="22" pageNumber="523">
Terminalia. Cercal plate and surstylus as in 
<figureCitation id="137EE1E1F47AFF9554D5FCBD2606FC8C" box="[688,817,834,859]" captionStart="FIGURES 73 – 88" captionStartId="23.[151,264,1941,1964]" captionTargetBox="[189,1406,191,1889]" captionTargetId="figure@23.[179,1408,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="FIGURES 73 – 88. Sternite 5; cercal plate and surstyli in dorsal view; epandrium, cercal plate and surstyli in lateral view; aedeagus in lateral view: 73 – 76. Limnophora parallelifrons Emden. 77 – 80. Limnophora perfida Stein. 81 – 84. Limnophora perfidodes Emden. 85 – 88. Limnophora praeapicalis Emden." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/242402/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="523">Figs 82–83</figureCitation>
. Aedeagal complex as in 
<figureCitation id="137EE1E1F47AFF95522AFCBD2196FC8C" box="[1103,1185,834,859]" captionStart="FIGURES 73 – 88" captionStartId="23.[151,264,1941,1964]" captionTargetBox="[189,1406,191,1889]" captionTargetId="figure@23.[179,1408,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="FIGURES 73 – 88. Sternite 5; cercal plate and surstyli in dorsal view; epandrium, cercal plate and surstyli in lateral view; aedeagus in lateral view: 73 – 76. Limnophora parallelifrons Emden. 77 – 80. Limnophora perfida Stein. 81 – 84. Limnophora perfidodes Emden. 85 – 88. Limnophora praeapicalis Emden." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/242402/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="523">Fig. 84</figureCitation>
.
</paragraph>
